"title": "7302: altar",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7302",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A construction, usually of wood, stone or metal, for the offering of sacrifice. The conflict between true and false religion often focused on altars, which were of key significance in biblical times.</p>\n<h2>Early altars built to the LORD</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:20\">GEN 8:20</a></strong> <em>These early altars were erected at sites where God's presence or power had been experienced.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:7-Gen12:8\">GEN 12:7–12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:18\">GEN 13:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:9\">GEN 22:9</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:25\">GEN 26:25</a> <em>by Isaac</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen33:20\">GEN 33:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:7\">GEN 35:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:15\">EXO 17:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:4\">EXO 24:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:30\">JOS 8:30</a> <em>by Joshua</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:24\">JDG 6:24</a> <em>by Gideon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:4\">JDG 21:4</a> <em>by unnamed Israelites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:17\">1SA 7:17</a> <em>by Samuel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:35\">1SA 14:35</a> <em>by Saul</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:25\">2SA 24:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:26\">1CH 21:26</a> <em>by David</em></p>\n<h2>Solomon's temple altar</h2>\n<p>It was preceded by the tabernacle altar of burnt offering:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:1-Exod27:8\">EXO 27:1–27:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:1-Exod30:10\">EXO 30:1–30:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:25-Exod37:28\">EXO 37:25–37:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:1-Exod38:7\">EXO 38:1–38:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:3-Heb9:4\">HEB 9:3–9:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:22\">1KI 8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:20\">1KI 6:20</a></p>\n<h2>OT pagan altars</h2>\n<h3>A symptom of decline in the northern kingdom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:32\">1KI 16:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:15\">2KI 23:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:11\">HOS 8:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:1\">HOS 10:1</a></p>\n<h3>A symptom of decline in the southern kingdom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:10\">2KI 16:10</a> <em>ignoring the command in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:2-Deut12:3\">Dt 12:2–3</a></em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:3\">2KI 21:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:8\">ISA 17:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:13\">JER 11:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:13\">JER 19:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:5\">ZEP 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Josiah's reform targeted illicit altars</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:12\">2KI 23:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:5\">DEU 7:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:8-Deut12:14\">DEU 12:8–12:14</a> <em>Josiah was implementing the law requiring sacrifice to be offered only on the altar at the sanctuary of God's choice</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:15-2Kgs23:20\">2KI 23:15–23:20</a></p>\n<h2>The altar in the second temple</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:2-Ezra3:3\">EZR 3:2–3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:17\">EZR 7:17</a></p>\n<h2>Laws concerning the altar of burnt offering</h2>\n<h3>Its construction</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:24-Exod20:26\">EXO 20:24–20:26</a></strong> <em>An earlier more basic form than in the tabernacle. No human hand was to shape the stones.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:1-Exod27:8\">EXO 27:1–27:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:1-Exod38:7\">EXO 38:1–38:7</a></p>\n<h3>Its use for the daily sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:38-Exod29:39\">EXO 29:38–29:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:28\">EXO 30:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:13\">NUM 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:10\">NUM 7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:84\">NUM 7:84</a></p>\n<h3>Its use for asylum</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:50-1Kgs1:51\">1KI 1:50–1:51</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:14\">EXO 21:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:28\">1KI 2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:14\">AMO 3:14</a></p>\n<h2>Laws concerning the incense altar</h2>\n<h3>Its construction</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:1-Exod30:5\">EXO 30:1–30:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:25-Exod37:28\">EXO 37:25–37:28</a></p>\n<h3>Its use</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:7\">EXO 30:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:8-Exod30:10\">EXO 30:8–30:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:11\">NUM 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>Altars in the NT</h2>\n<h3>The Jerusalem temple altar</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:23-Matt5:24\">MAT 5:23–5:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:18-Matt23:20\">MAT 23:18–23:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:13\">1CO 9:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:18\">1CO 10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:13\">HEB 7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:4\">HEB 9:4</a></p>\n<h3>Pagan altars</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:23\">ACT 17:23</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The cross as an ``altar''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:10\">HEB 13:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Altars in heaven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:9\">REV 6:9</a></strong> <em>The lives of martyred saints are compared to the blood of offerings poured out at the base of the altar</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:3\">REV 8:3</a></strong> <em>The prayers of God's people are like incense, offered to him on the heavenly altar.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:13\">REV 9:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:1\">REV 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:18\">REV 14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:7\">REV 16:7</a></p>",
